```markdown
# 📚 Cybersecurity Reading List — GitHub Edition

A curated set of books to deepen your understanding across beginner, intermediate, and advanced levels. Ideal for pairing with Udemy courses, Cisco Networking Academy modules, and governance-aligned certification tracks.

---

## 🧠 Beginner-Level Reads

| **Title**                                | **Author**           | **Why It’s Valuable**                                                                 |
|------------------------------------------|----------------------|----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------|
| Cybersecurity For Dummies                | Joseph Steinberg     | Friendly intro to threats, data protection, and basic network security.               |
| Cybersecurity for Beginners              | Raef Meeuwisse       | Covers the landscape of cyber threats and defense strategies in plain language.       |
| How Cybersecurity Really Works           | Sam Grubb            | Hands-on guide with real-world examples—ideal for total beginners.                    |

---

## 🚀 Intermediate-Level Reads

| **Title**                                | **Author**           | **Why It’s Valuable**                                                                 |
|------------------------------------------|----------------------|----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------|
| The Hacker Playbook 3                    | Peter Kim            | Practical penetration testing scenarios and red team tactics.                         |
| Cybersecurity Essentials                 | Charles J. Brooks    | Explains threat agents, vulnerabilities, and security frameworks.                     |
| Hacking: The Art of Exploitation         | Jon Erickson         | Deep dive into the hacker mindset, programming, and network exploitation.             |

---

## 🔐 Advanced-Level Reads

| **Title**                                | **Author**           | **Why It’s Valuable**                                                                 |
|------------------------------------------|----------------------|----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------|
| The Art of Invisibility                  | Kevin Mitnick        | Privacy strategies from one of the world’s most famous hackers.                       |
| Blue Team Handbook                       | Don Murdoch          | Incident response and defense tactics for SOC analysts.                               |
| CISSP All-in-One Exam Guide              | Shon Harris          | Comprehensive prep for governance, risk, and compliance leadership roles.             |

---

## 🛡️ Governance & Responsible AI Tie-In

| **Title**                                | **Author/Publisher** | **Why It’s Valuable**                                                                 |
|------------------------------------------|----------------------|----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------|
| Security Engineering                     | Ross Anderson        | Explores system design, trust models, and policy enforcement.                         |
| Ethics of Cybersecurity                  | Springer Open Access | Discusses ethical frameworks and governance in digital systems.                       |
| Privacy is Power                         | Carissa Véliz        | A philosophical and practical guide to data rights and digital autonomy.              |

---

## ✅ Reading Tracker Template

```markdown
- [x] Cybersecurity For Dummies
- [ ] The Hacker Playbook 3
- [ ] CISSP All-in-One Exam Guide
- [ ] Privacy is Power
```

---

> 💡 Tip: Fork this list into your GitHub repo and update progress weekly. Use issues or pull requests to reflect insights or link to notes.

```
